{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862868530,"sessionID":"ses_286539de0ffeA96R5fMXgNP0FG","part":{"id":"prt_d79ace7a30015AtIGHlZ0vqzjV","messageID":"msg_d79acdec1001V9rykacWJfdkVE","sessionID":"ses_286539de0ffeA96R5fMXgNP0FG","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-3a72d10bae3d45f9beb4aba08c1c6c3c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Deploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation\n9: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n13: - **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n14: - **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\n17: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n20: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values\n21: - **WHEN** pods for `workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router` start\n22: - **THEN** each container SHALL have environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` populated from those values\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Workload Manager deployment shape\n25: The system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with replica count, container image, service type/port, resource requests/limits, health probes, and optional `extraEnv` driven from `values.yaml`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Default replica and service exposure\n28: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n29: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n30: - **THEN** the Workload Manager `Deployment` SHALL use `workloadmanager.replicas` (default 1), expose HTTP on `workloadmanager.service.port` (default 8080), and use liveness/readiness HTTP GET `/health` on that port\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Router deployment shape\n33: The system SHALL deploy the Router as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `agentcube-router` with replica count, image, `ClusterIP` service mapping `port`→`targetPort`, resource requests/limits, optional dedicated `serviceAccountName`, and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` pointing at the in-cluster Workload Manager service.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router reaches Workload Manager by DNS\n36: - **GIVEN** release namespace `N` and Workload Manager service port `P` from values\n37: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL have `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` set to `http://workloadmanager.N.svc.cluster.local:P` and container args including `--port=<targetPort>` and `--debug`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Workload Manager ClusterRole permissions\n41: The system SHALL create a `ServiceAccount` `workloadmanager`, a `ClusterRole` `workloadmanager`, and `ClusterRoleBinding` `workloadmanager` granting the rules required for agent-sandbox, AgentCube runtime CRDs, core workloads, auth, and secrets.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Binding ties SA to cluster role\n44: - **GIVEN** chart installation in namespace `N`\n45: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n46: - **THEN** subject `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `N` SHALL be bound to `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` via `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Optional Router namespace Role\n49: The system SHALL optionally create namespace-scoped `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router when `router.rbac.create` is true, granting secret management in that namespace.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: RBAC off by default\n52: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false`\n53: - **WHEN** the chart renders templates\n54: - **THEN** Router optional RBAC manifests SHALL NOT be emitted\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: RBAC on with named service account\n57: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` and `router.serviceAccountName` set (or defaulted by template to `agentcube-router`)\n58: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n59: - **THEN** Router pods MAY use that `serviceAccountName` and the Role SHALL allow verbs on `secrets` in the release namespace\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Optional Volcano agent scheduler\n62: The system SHALL optionally deploy Volcano agent scheduler resources (ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Scheduler disabled\n65: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n66: - **WHEN** templates render\n67: - **THEN** no Volcano scheduler objects SHALL be created\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: CRDs shipped with the chart\n70: The system SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` under the chart `crds/` directory so Helm installs them with the chart lifecycle.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: CRD group and scope\n73: - **GIVEN** chart path `manifests/charts/base`\n74: - **WHEN** CRD YAML is applied\n75: - **THEN** both CRDs SHALL use API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, and `scope: Namespaced`\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Docker images for core binaries\n78: The system SHALL provide Dockerfiles to build three images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`), Router (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Multi-stage Go build for control plane\n81: - **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n82: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile` (or `Dockerfile.router`) runs\n83: - **THEN** the image SHALL compile the respective Go binary with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and run it from Alpine 3.19 as a non-root user (`apiserver` UID 1000 or `router` UID 1000) exposing port 8080\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Makefile build targets\n86: The system SHALL expose Make targets to build binaries (`build`, related targets), run tests (`test`), build/push Docker images (`docker-*`), run code generation (`generate`, `gen-crd`, `gen-client`, `gen-all`, `gen-check`), and run E2E (`e2e`, `e2e-clean`).\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default `make` builds workload manager\n89: - **GIVEN** Go toolchain and generated code prerequisites\n90: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make` (default `all` → `build`)\n91: - **THEN** `bin/workloadmanager` SHALL be produced from `./cmd/workload-manager` after `generate`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: E2E entrypoint\n94: - **GIVEN** Kind, kubectl, Docker, Helm, and curl available\n95: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make e2e`\n96: - **THEN** the repository SHALL execute `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` which provisions the cluster (unless skipped), deploys dependencies, and runs Go and Python E2E tests\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Specification\n\n## Purpose\nDeploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Helm chart installation\nThe system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n\n#### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n- **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n\n### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\nThe system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n\n#### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/spec.md","time":{"start":1775862868510,"end":1775862868528}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862868534,"sessionID":"ses_286539de0ffeA96R5fMXgNP0FG","part":{"id":"prt_d79acea0b001Z64Lji2s9Zjdrk","messageID":"msg_d79acdec1001V9rykacWJfdkVE","sessionID":"ses_286539de0ffeA96R5fMXgNP0FG","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-1928ff847f2842bd97b9aa54fa49f509","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # pkg/apis — CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition Design\n2: \n3: ## AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition\n4: \n5: **Module**: `pkg/apis`  \n6: **Language**: Go  \n7: **Size**: S  \n8: **Purpose**: Define Kubernetes CRDs for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, enable client-go generation, and provide type-safe API access.\n9: \n10: ## Architecture\n11: \n12: ### Package Structure\n13: \n14: ```\n15: pkg/apis/\n16: ├── runtime/\n17: │   └── v1alpha1/\n18: │       ├── agentruntime_types.go   # AgentRuntime spec/status\n19: │       ├── codeinterpreter_types.go # CodeInterpreter spec/status\n20: │       ├── doc.go                   # Package documentation\n21: │       ├── groupversion_info.go     # GroupVersion constants\n22: │       ├── register.go              # Scheme registration\n23: │       └── zz_generated.deepcopy.go # DeepCopy methods (controller-gen)\n24: client-go/                          # Generated client library\n25: └── runtime/\n26:     └── v1alpha1/                   # Generated types (symlink or copy)\n27: ```\n28: \n29: ### API Group\n30: \n31: - **Group**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n32: - **Version**: `v1alpha1`\n33: - **Scope**: `Namespaced`\n34: \n35: ### Component Interactions\n36: \n37: ```\n38: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n39: │                    Kubernetes API Server                │\n40: │                                                          │\n41: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n42: │  │         runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1    │  │\n43: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n44: │  │  │  agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh │  │  │\n45: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n46: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n47: │  │  │  codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh││  │\n48: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n49: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n50: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n51:                           │\n52:                           │ k8s client-go\n53:                           ▼\n54: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n55: │                 client-go (Generated)                   │\n56: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n57: │  │  clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/     │  │\n58: │  │    • AgentRuntimeInterface                       │  │\n59: │  │    • CodeInterpreterInterface                    │  │\n60: │  │    • REST CRUD + Watch                           │  │\n61: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n62: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n63: │  │  informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/    │  │\n64: │  │    • AgentRuntimeInformer                        │  │\n65: │  │    • CodeInterpreterInformer                     │  │\n66: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n67: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n68: │  │  listers/runtime/v1alpha1/                      │  │\n69: │  │    • AgentRuntimeLister                          │  │\n70: │  │    • CodeInterpreterLister                       │  │\n71: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n72: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n73: ```\n74: \n75: ## Data Structures\n76: \n77: ### AgentRuntime\n78: \n79: **File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n80: \n81: ```go\n82: // AgentRuntimeSpec defines the desired state of AgentRuntime\n83: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n84:     // MaxSessionDuration is the maximum duration for any session\n85:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n86:     MaxSessionDuration string `json:\"maxSessionDuration\"`\n87:     \n88:     // SessionTimeout is the idle timeout before a session is terminated\n89:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n90:     SessionTimeout string `json:\"sessionTimeout\"`\n91:     \n92:     // TargetPort specifies the HTTP/HTTPS ports to expose\n93:     // +kubebuilder:validation:MinItems=1\n94:     TargetPort []TargetPort `json:\"targetPort\"`\n95:     \n96:     // PodTemplate defines the pod template for agent sandbox pods\n97:     PodTemplate PodTemplateSpec `json:\"podTemplate\"`\n98: }\n99: \n100: // AgentRuntimeStatus defines the observed state of AgentRuntime\n101: type AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n102:     // Conditions represent the latest available observations\n103:     Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n104:     \n105:     // ObservedGeneration is the most recent generation observed\n106:     ObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n107: }\n108: \n109: // TargetPort defines a single HTTP/HTTPS port target\n110: type TargetPort struct {\n111:     // Port is the port number\n112:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n113:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n114:     Port int32 `json:\"port\"`\n115:     \n116:     // Protocol must be \"HTTP\" or \"HTTPS\"\n117:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS\n118:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n119:     \n120:     // Name is an optional name for the port\n121:     Name string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n122:     \n123:     // PathPrefix is the URL path prefix for this port\n124:     PathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n125: }\n126: \n127: // PodTemplateSpec defines the pod template specification\n128: type PodTemplateSpec struct {\n129:     // Metadata for the pod\n130:     Metadata metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n131:     \n132:     // Spec for the pod\n133:     Spec PodSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n134: }\n135: \n136: // AgentRuntime is the Schema for the agentruntimes API\n137: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n138: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n139: // +kubebuilder:resource:shortName=art\n140: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n141: type AgentRuntime struct {\n142:     metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n143:     metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n144:     \n145:     Spec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n146:     Status AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n147: }\n148: \n149: // AgentRuntimeList contains a list of AgentRuntime\n150: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n151: type AgentRuntimeList struct {\n152:     metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n153:     metav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n154:     \n155:     Items []AgentRuntime `json:\"items\"`\n156: }\n157: ```\n158: \n159: ### CodeInterpreter\n160: \n161: **File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n162: \n163: ```go\n164: // CodeInterpreterSpec defines the desired state of CodeInterpreter\n165: type CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n166:     // AuthMode specifies the authentication mode\n167:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"picod\"\n168:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=picod;none\n169:     AuthMode string `json:\"authMode\"`\n170:     \n171:     // MaxSessionDuration is the maximum duration for any session\n172:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n173:     MaxSessionDuration string `json:\"maxSessionDuration\"`\n174:     \n175:     // SessionTimeout is the idle timeout before a session is terminated\n176:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n177:     SessionTimeout string `json:\"sessionTimeout\"`\n178:     \n179:     // Ports specifies the HTTP/HTTPS ports to expose\n180:     // +kubebuilder:validation:MinItems=1\n181:     Ports []TargetPort `json:\"ports\"`\n182:     \n183:     // Template defines the pod template for code interpreter pods\n184:     Template InterpreterTemplateSpec `json:\"template\"`\n185:     \n186:     // WarmPoolSize is the size of the warm pool\n187:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n188:     WarmPoolSize int32 `json:\"warmPoolSize,omitempty\"`\n189: }\n190: \n191: // CodeInterpreterStatus defines the observed state of CodeInterpreter\n192: type CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n193:     // Conditions represent the latest available observations\n194:     Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n195:     \n196:     // Ready indicates the code interpreter is ready\n197:     Ready bool `json:\"ready,omitempty\"`\n198:     \n199:     // ObservedGeneration is the most recent generation observed\n200:     ObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n201: }\n202: \n203: // InterpreterTemplateSpec defines the interpreter pod template\n204: type InterpreterTemplateSpec struct {\n205:     // Metadata for the pod\n206:     Metadata metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n207:     \n208:     // Spec for the pod\n209:     Spec PodSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n210: }\n211: \n212: // PodSpec defines the pod specification (subset of core v1.PodSpec)\n213: type PodSpec struct {\n214:     // Containers in the pod\n215:     Containers []Container `json:\"containers,omitempty\"`\n216:     \n217:     // Init containers\n218:     InitContainers []Container `json:\"initContainers,omitempty\"`\n219:     \n220:     // Volumes in the pod\n221:     Volumes []Volume `json:\"volumes,omitempty\"`\n222:     \n223:     // Restart policy\n224:     RestartPolicy string `json:\"restartPolicy,omitempty\"`\n225:     \n226:     // Service account name\n227:     ServiceAccountName string `json:\"serviceAccountName,omitempty\"`\n228:     \n229:     // Runtime class name\n230:     RuntimeClassName string `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n231:     \n232:     // Node selector\n233:     NodeSelector map[string]string `json:\"nodeSelector,omitempty\"`\n234:     \n235:     // Affinity rules\n236:     Affinity *Affinity `json:\"affinity,omitempty\"`\n237:     \n238:     // Tolerations\n239:     Tolerations []Toleration `json:\"tolerations,omitempty\"`\n240:     \n241:     // Resource requirements\n242:     Resources *ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n243: }\n244: \n245: // Container defines a container in the pod\n246: type Container struct {\n247:     Name            string            `json:\"name\"`\n248:     Image           string            `json:\"image\"`\n249:     Command         []string          `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n250:     Args            []string          `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n251:     WorkingDir      string            `json:\"workingDir,omitempty\"`\n252:     Ports           []ContainerPort   `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n253:     Env             []EnvVar          `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n254:     Resources       *ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n255:     VolumeMounts    []VolumeMount     `json:\"volumeMounts,omitempty\"`\n256:     LivenessProbe   *Probe            `json:\"livenessProbe,omitempty\"`\n257:     ReadinessProbe  *Probe            `json:\"readinessProbe,omitempty\"`\n258:     SecurityContext *SecurityContext   `json:\"securityContext,omitempty\"`\n259: }\n260: \n261: // CodeInterpreter is the Schema for the codeinterpreters API\n262: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n263: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n264: // +kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ci\n265: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Ready\",type=\"boolean\",JSONPath=\".status.ready\"\n266: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n267: type CodeInterpreter struct {\n268:     metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n269:     metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n270:     \n271:     Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n272:     Status CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n273: }\n274: \n275: // CodeInterpreterList contains a list of CodeInterpreter\n276: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n277: type CodeInterpreterList struct {\n278:     metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n279:     metav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n280:     \n281:     Items []CodeInterpreter `json:\"items\"`\n282: }\n283: ```\n284: \n285: ### Helper Types\n286: \n287: **File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n288: \n289: ```go\n290: // ContainerPort defines a container port\n291: type ContainerPort struct {\n292:     Name          string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n293:     ContainerPort int32  `json:\"containerPort\"`\n294:     Protocol      string `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n295:     HostPort      int32  `json:\"hostPort,omitempty\"`\n296: }\n297: \n298: // EnvVar defines an environment variable\n299: type EnvVar struct {\n300:     Name  string      `json:\"name\"`\n301:     Value string      `json:\"value,omitempty\"`\n302:     ValueFrom *EnvVarSource `json:\"valueFrom,omitempty\"`\n303: }\n304: \n305: // EnvVarSource defines a source for environment variable\n306: type EnvVarSource struct {\n307:     FieldRef *ObjectFieldSelector `json:\"fieldRef,omitempty\"`\n308: }\n309: \n310: // ObjectFieldSelector selects a field from an object\n311: type ObjectFieldSelector struct {\n312:     FieldPath string `json:\"fieldPath\"`\n313: }\n314: \n315: // ResourceRequirements describes compute resource requirements\n316: type ResourceRequirements struct {\n317:     Limits   ResourceList `json:\"limits,omitempty\"`\n318:     Requests ResourceList `json:\"requests,omitempty\"`\n319: }\n320: \n321: // ResourceList is a set of resource names and quantities\n322: type ResourceList map[string]string\n323: \n324: // Volume defines a volume\n325: type Volume struct {\n326:     Name   string      `json:\"name\"`\n327:     Secret *SecretVolumeSource `json:\"secret,omitempty\"`\n328:     ConfigMap *ConfigMapVolumeSource `json:\"configMap,omitempty\"`\n329:     EmptyDir *EmptyDirVolumeSource `json:\"emptyDir,omitempty\"`\n330: }\n331: \n332: // SecretVolumeSource adapts a Secret into a volume\n333: type SecretVolumeSource struct {\n334:     SecretName string `json:\"secretName\"`\n335: }\n336: \n337: // ConfigMapVolumeSource adapts a ConfigMap into a volume\n338: type ConfigMapVolumeSource struct {\n339:     LocalObjectReference `json:\",inline\"`\n340: }\n341: \n342: // EmptyDirVolumeSource represents an empty directory for a pod\n343: type EmptyDirVolumeSource struct {\n344:     Medium string `json:\"medium,omitempty\"`\n345: }\n346: \n347: // VolumeMount defines a volume mount\n348: type VolumeMount struct {\n349:     Name      string `json:\"name\"`\n350:     MountPath string `json:\"mountPath\"`\n351:     ReadOnly  bool   `json:\"readOnly,omitempty\"`\n352: }\n353: \n354: // Probe defines a health check\n355: type Probe struct {\n356:     ProbeHandler `json:\",inline\"`\n357:     InitialDelaySeconds int32 `json:\"initialDelaySeconds,omitempty\"`\n358:     TimeoutSeconds      int32 `json:\"timeoutSeconds,omitempty\"`\n359:     PeriodSeconds       int32 `json:\"periodSeconds,omitempty\"`\n360:     SuccessThreshold    int32 `json:\"successThreshold,omitempty\"`\n361:     FailureThreshold    int32 `json:\"failureThreshold,omitempty\"`\n362: }\n363: \n364: // ProbeHandler defines a handler for a probe\n365: type ProbeHandler struct {\n366:     HTTPGet *HTTPGetAction `json:\"httpGet,omitempty\"`\n367:     Exec    *ExecAction    `json:\"exec,omitempty\"`\n368:     TCPSocket *TCPSocketAction `json:\"tcpSocket,omitempty\"`\n369: }\n370: \n371: // HTTPGetAction defines an HTTP GET r